1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,890
[Lee Dong Won as Seung Jun]

2
00:00:07,890 --> 00:00:09,530
[Seong Tae as Jae Hyeon]

3
00:00:09,530 --> 00:00:11,280
[Shin Myeong Seong as Ho Yeon]

4
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:13,050
[Kim Gyu Jong as Ju Won]

5
00:00:35,598 --> 00:00:43,598
[Happy Merry Ending]

6
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,300
Focus.

7
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:53,512
A beautiful melody fills the hall.

8
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:56,267
And you meet my eyes

9
00:00:56,267 --> 00:00:58,650
before you start singing.

10
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,751
And...

11
00:01:02,751 --> 00:01:05,000
You close your eyes

12
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:09,326
Imagine that there's only you and me there.

13
00:01:12,670 --> 00:01:14,709
What is that supposed to mean?

14
00:01:14,709 --> 00:01:16,109
You never know.

15
00:01:16,109 --> 00:01:19,384
You might sing better when I'm the only one you can see.

16
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:21,892
Now try it.

17
00:01:21,892 --> 00:01:23,350
No.

18
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:25,042
Try it.

19
00:01:25,042 --> 00:01:26,999
I just cast a spell on you.

20
00:01:26,999 --> 00:01:29,118
I said no.

21
00:01:29,118 --> 00:01:30,709
Just this once!

22
00:01:30,709 --> 00:01:31,919
Forget it.

23
00:01:31,919 --> 00:01:34,293
Now is the perfect time to...

24
00:01:34,293 --> 00:01:36,818
Hey, Ho Yeon!

25
00:01:43,234 --> 00:01:50,225
[Episode 5: Skinship With Him]

26
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,292
Who is this?

27
00:01:52,292 --> 00:01:56,267
This is Song Jae Hyeon, who will be taking classes from me starting today.

28
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:58,709
I mean... he's Jae Hyeon Hyeong.

29
00:02:01,010 --> 00:02:04,992
- Hi, I'm Song Jae Hyeon.
- Okay.

30
00:02:04,992 --> 00:02:07,727
And this is my friend, Im Ho Yeon. He lives upstairs.

31
00:02:07,727 --> 00:02:09,412
I see.

32
00:02:11,690 --> 00:02:14,167
I didn't realize it was so late.

33
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:16,542
Seung Jun, I should get going.

34
00:02:16,542 --> 00:02:18,559
See you again, Ho Yeon.

35
00:02:18,559 --> 00:02:21,334
Yeah, hurry home safely.

36
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:36,767
You finished early.

37
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:40,142
I'm relieved to see that you look happier than you did a while ago.

38
00:02:40,142 --> 00:02:42,262
- Good night.
- Are you going home?

39
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:43,918
Let's eat together!

40
00:02:43,918 --> 00:02:46,050
I already ate.

41
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:28,742
[You must be busy. When can we meet?]

42
00:03:33,392 --> 00:03:36,159
Why was he looking for me?

43
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:38,017
Seung Jun!

44
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:40,542
I've been calling you for a while.

45
00:03:40,542 --> 00:03:42,967
Sorry, I didn't hear you.

46
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,700
Let's go in.

47
00:03:53,850 --> 00:03:57,934
Next up is a song to celebrate the bright future of the bride and groom!

48
00:03:57,934 --> 00:04:01,335
Please give them a round of applause.

49
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:45,242
♪ Your smiling face keeps appearing in my mind ♪

50
00:04:45,242 --> 00:04:51,018
♪ One day, suddenly, you became a part of my daily life ♪

51
00:04:51,018 --> 00:04:56,851
♪ I imagine the things I want to do when I meet you ♪

52
00:04:56,851 --> 00:05:03,450
♪ And by doing so, even a typical boring day ♪
♪ Becomes special ♪

53
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:08,160
♪ Ever since I met you, ♪

54
00:05:09,325 --> 00:05:19,425
♪ All the moments in my ordinary, daily life have become ♪

55
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:22,746
Did you like my sunglasses?

56
00:05:22,746 --> 00:05:26,325
I almost made a mistake... Please don't do that again.

57
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:31,034
It's nice to see you smile.

58
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:38,992
I shouldn't have said that.

59
00:05:38,992 --> 00:05:40,993
There's that startled expression again.

60
00:05:40,993 --> 00:05:43,710
It's just that it's really nice to see you smile!

61
00:05:45,090 --> 00:05:47,122
You don't have classes today, right?

62
00:05:47,122 --> 00:05:49,197
I'll drive you home.

63
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:07,027
Seung Jun.

64
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:13,224
- Seung Jun!
- What?

65
00:06:13,224 --> 00:06:16,960
Why are you staring at your phone? Are you waiting for a call?

66
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,628
No.

67
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:22,494
But there is someone I hope never calls.

68
00:06:27,810 --> 00:06:30,485
I have to stop by some place.

69
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,777
Where is he?

70
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:02,803
What the...

71
00:07:02,803 --> 00:07:04,852
Are you up?

72
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:07,902
Why did you come here?

73
00:07:07,902 --> 00:07:10,042
Something is troubling you, isn't it?

74
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:14,810
But you wouldn't tell me even if I asked.

75
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:17,519
So I'm just going to stay with you.

76
00:07:21,610 --> 00:07:24,235
I'll keep this with me for a while.

77
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,845
Should we take a walk?

78
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:56,220
♫ By the time the sun sets and the skies fade to red ♫

79
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,685
How is it?

80
00:07:59,685 --> 00:08:01,810
This is nice.

81
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:04,827
No more complicated thoughts.

82
00:08:04,827 --> 00:08:07,728
I like it, too.

83
00:08:07,728 --> 00:08:09,452
Do you come here often?

84
00:08:09,452 --> 00:08:13,202
Yes. When I'm frustrated...

85
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:15,744
When I want to listen...

86
00:08:15,744 --> 00:08:18,077
When I wonder what you're doing.

87
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:24,261
When I miss you.

88
00:08:24,261 --> 00:08:27,328
That is why I come to see you.

89
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:31,778
Why are you being like this...

90
00:08:31,778 --> 00:08:34,238
to someone like me?

91
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,794
I've never done anything like this before, either.

92
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:42,988
But I just want to stay by your side...

93
00:08:42,988 --> 00:08:45,002
and protect you.

94
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,944
I can't resist anymore.

95
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:55,644
Can I kiss you?

96
00:08:57,770 --> 00:09:04,840
♫ Because I grew it just for you ♫

97
00:09:31,530 --> 00:09:34,501
Where the hell is he, and what is he up to?

98
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:56,570
This guy has been calling for a while.

99
00:09:56,570 --> 00:09:58,510
Are you sure you don't have to pick up?

100
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:04,410
Yes, it's fine.

101
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,350
Who is it?

102
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:10,428
The man who made me like this.

103
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:21,495
It's been so long since I felt this peaceful.

104
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:30,345
I couldn't stop thinking about you.

105
00:10:42,890 --> 00:10:45,412
- See, I told you it doesn't work!
- Wait. Move, move.

106
00:10:45,412 --> 00:10:47,079
- Is it okay?
- Yeah.

107
00:10:47,079 --> 00:10:48,315
How is this?

108
00:10:48,315 --> 00:10:50,560
Wow! It suits you!

109
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:53,370
Two, one!

110
00:10:53,370 --> 00:10:59,220
♫ One day, suddenly, you became a part of my daily life ♫

111
00:10:59,220 --> 00:11:02,870
♫ I imagine the things I want to do when I meet you ♫

112
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,414
- Ducks!
- Where?

113
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:06,622
There! Ducks!

114
00:11:06,622 --> 00:11:07,960
That's cute.

115
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:12,130
♫ Becomes special ♫

116
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,787
Wow. What is this?

117
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,037
I made it.

118
00:11:29,037 --> 00:11:32,101
- You made it yourself?
- Of course! Try it.

119
00:11:32,101 --> 00:11:34,612
- I want to try it.
- Go ahead.

120
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:41,423
How is it? It's good, right?

121
00:11:41,423 --> 00:11:43,645
Really good.

122
00:11:44,570 --> 00:11:47,666
I can make it for you every day.

123
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:50,271
- Really?
- Of course.

124
00:11:50,271 --> 00:11:52,821
Chew before you swallow.

125
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:02,396
And remember to relax your lips when you practice.

126
00:12:02,396 --> 00:12:03,896
Yes!

127
00:12:03,896 --> 00:12:06,680
Hm... But why isn't this coming off...

128
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:11,029
Thank you very much!

129
00:12:11,029 --> 00:12:13,013
Yes, good job today.

130
00:12:16,890 --> 00:12:18,624
Chan Wu.

131
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:22,717
Why don't you try taking another teacher's class?

132
00:12:22,717 --> 00:12:24,605
What?

133
00:12:24,605 --> 00:12:26,063
Why?

134
00:12:26,063 --> 00:12:28,688
I don't want to. I like you.

135
00:12:28,688 --> 00:12:31,893
The CEO told me he likes you, too.

136
00:12:31,893 --> 00:12:34,938
Dance songs aren't really my area of expertise.

137
00:12:34,938 --> 00:12:38,038
And I was planning on getting some time off from the academy.

138
00:12:38,038 --> 00:12:41,021
Oh, I see.

139
00:12:41,021 --> 00:12:42,871
That's a shame.

140
00:12:42,871 --> 00:12:44,826
I'll see you out.

141
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:54,038
Get back safely.

142
00:12:54,038 --> 00:12:57,230
Teacher, does that mean we won't be seeing each other?

143
00:12:57,230 --> 00:12:59,353
It's not like we will never see each other again if we don't meet here anymore.

144
00:12:59,353 --> 00:13:01,114
You can call me if something happens.

145
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:03,383
Oh! Thank you, Teacher.

146
00:13:03,383 --> 00:13:05,876
Can I call you often?

147
00:13:05,876 --> 00:13:07,580
Not too often.

148
00:13:07,580 --> 00:13:09,680
Okay.

149
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:14,349
Oh! It's the CEO! CEO!

150
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:28,652
Chan Wu, can you wait for me in the car for a little while?

151
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,905
Yes.

152
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,021
How have you been?

153
00:13:40,021 --> 00:13:43,021
What are you doing?

154
00:13:43,021 --> 00:13:44,670
What does it look like?

155
00:13:44,670 --> 00:13:48,170
I'm just picking up my trainee.

156
00:13:48,170 --> 00:13:50,122
Did you send him here on purpose?

157
00:13:50,122 --> 00:13:51,955
Isn't Chan Wu nice?

158
00:13:51,955 --> 00:13:54,341
I thought you two would get along.

159
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:59,422
He is a lot like you.

160
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:07,130
You must be having a hard time. Your face looks rough.

161
00:14:12,630 --> 00:14:16,080
My little Seung Jun, you used to be so nice when you were younger.

162
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:18,497
If you don't have anything to say, I will leave now.

163
00:14:18,497 --> 00:14:20,330
What's the rush?

164
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:23,288
I have a proposal for you.

165
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:51,490
♫ By the time the sun sets and the skies fade to red ♫

166
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:58,830
♫ And I watch our shadows grow longer ♫

167
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:05,870
♫ Even if there are no expressions or words left to say ♫
